Description: ConnectUp makes it easy to reach the people who matter, whether a business associate or a personal friend.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: People are social beings. Since the early days of the human race, those with the ability to develop and maintain many mutually beneficial relationships enjoyed more successes in life, whether at work, at home, in a small town or big society. In fact, most successful people know their achievements are due to the help they received from others.  The recent phenomenon of social networking promised to be the next level of connecting, only to leave us all overwhelmed. People have become "hyperconnected," with access to more contacts and data than ever before, and yet... social media does almost nothing to help build strong relationships. We call it hyperconnectedness because people are linked in some way to between 1,000 to 3,000 people, but without prompting, the human mind cannot remember more than 400-500. How odd then, that when you need someone most, you have forgotten them and in many cases they have forgotten you.  ConnectUp makes it easy to reach the people who matter, whether a business associate or a personal friend. Extending a personal touch at the right time to the right person makes all the difference in getting others to think of you. To remember you. The most successful people know this and they are better than most of us at connecting, but even the best super-connectors sense a constant pang of letting far too many relationships fade.  Welcome to the next era of technology, the era that makes you more human, not less. Discover for yourself the tremendous value of more and better relationships. Discover ConnectUp.  ConnectUp is lead by a team of executives with backgrounds creating and launching billion dollar consumer technology businesses. With experience from Microsoft, Razorfish, LendingClub, Expedia, GoPro, and Orbitz, among others, the team knows what it takes to create and deliver technology that makes a real difference. The team knows how important it is for the right people to connect at the right time to create success.  Backed by Mohr Davidow Ventures and a group of prominent Silicon Valley angel investors, ConnectUp was born of the burning desire of its founders to leverage the latest AI technologies to empower individuals to ignite, leverage and optimize their networks in a human way.
Industry Groups: Apps, Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Information Technology, Internet Services, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: Aaron Tillman, founder of Tillman Law, fights for justice in personal injury cases. No upfront fees, 24/7 consultations.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Aaron Tillman serves as the founding attorney at Tillman Law Personal Injury Lawyers, a firm committed to prioritizing its clients' needs. His legal practice focuses on a range of personal injury cases, including car accidents, motorcycle accidents, truck accidents, medical malpractice, wrongful death, and more. Mr. Tillman obtained his Juris Doctor from Gonzaga University School of Law in Spokane, Washington, in 2005, followed by a Master of Law from Boston University School of Law in 2006. He is licensed to practice law in Oregon and Utah. At Tillman Law Personal Injury Lawyers, we understand the daunting process of dealing with insurance companies, especially when you're already grappling with pain, injuries, and the effort to rebuild your life. Managing medical expenses and lost wages adds to the stress, and confronting insurance companies with their experienced legal teams for a fair settlement can be overwhelming. This is where we step in. Aaron Tillman takes pride in guiding his clients through these challenging times and vigorously advocating for justice on their behalf. He ensures that your rights are safeguarded to the fullest extent and strives for a just settlement. If the insurance company refuses to provide a reasonable offer at the negotiation table, Mr. Tillman will not hesitate to take them to court to secure the compensation you rightfully deserve. Tillman Law Personal Injury Lawyers operates on a contingency basis, which means you won't incur any upfront legal fees. Our Portland personal injury lawyers are available for calls and texts 24/7, and we invite you to schedule a free consultation at your convenience.
